== Snapshot server

A small rails application for serving OpenStreetMap map-calls. This is based on a database loaded with the osmosis pg-snapshot database format

== Installation

createdb -E utf8 snapshot-dev
createlang plpgsql snapshot-dev
psql -f /usr/share/postgresql/8.4/contrib/hstore.sql snapshot-dev
psql -f /usr/share/postgresql/8.4/contrib/postgis-1.5/postgis.sql snapshot-dev
psql -f /usr/share/postgresql/8.4/contrib/postgis-1.5/spatial_ref_sys.sql snapshot-dev 
psql -f /home/andy/bin/osmosis/osmosis-0.39/script/pgsnapshot_schema_0.6.sql snapshot-dev

Then load the data using osmosis --read-xml --write-pgsql

After the data is loaded, you need to run rake db:migrate in order to add the status columns.
